reference:
  MaxDB PHP Extension
  MaxDB




    &reftitle.intro;


     The MaxDB PHP extension allows you to access the functionality provided by
     MaxDB 7.5.0 and above. More information about the MaxDB Database server
     can be found at &url.maxdb;.



     The MaxDB PHP extension is compatible to the MySQL mysqli extension. There are only
     minor differences in the behaviour of some functions due to the differences of the
     underlying database servers, MaxDB and MySQL.



     The main differences to mysqli are in the following functions:


    maxdb_character_set_name - returns only ascii or unicode
    maxdb_disable_reads_from_master - function is experimental
    maxdb_disable_rpl_parse - function is experimental
    maxdb_dump_debug_info - function is experimental
    maxdb_embedded_connect - function is experimental
    maxdb_enable_reads_from_master - function is experimental
    maxdb_enable_rpl_parse - function is experimental
    maxdb_get_client_info - different version string
    maxdb_get_client_version - different version string
    maxdb_get_host_info - returns localhost or hostname
    maxdb_get_server_info - different version string
    maxdb_get_server_version - different version string
    maxdb_kill - disconnects session
    maxdb_master_query - function is experimental
    maxdb_more_results - functions returns always false
    maxdb_multi_query - can not handle multiple SQL statements
    maxdb_next_result - functions returns always false
    maxdb_options - different set of options
    maxdb_report - different report modes
    maxdb_rpl_parse_enabled - function is experimental
    maxdb_rpl_probe - function is experimental
    maxdb_rpl_query_type - function is experimental
    maxdb_send_query - function is experimental
    maxdb_server_end - function is experimental
    maxdb_server_init - function is experimental
    maxdb_ssl_set - function is experimental
    maxdb_stat - different system status
    maxdb_stmt_store_result - has no effect
    maxdb_store_result - has no effect



     Documentation for MaxDB can be found at
     &url.maxdb.doc;.





    &reftitle.required;


     In order to have these functions available, you must compile PHP with
     MaxDB support.Additionally, you must have the MaxDB SQLDBC runtime library
     available to access the MaxDB server. 



     Documentation for MaxDB SQLDBC can be found at
     &url.maxdb.doc;.



     Download the MaxDB SQLDBC package from 
     &url.maxdb.sdbc;.




